<TITLE> Nimchandra won't leave jail without colleagues: lawyer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnewes24.com)  Professor Nimchandra Bhowmick has said he will not leave the jail without his colleagues sentenced to two years in jail for breaking emergency rule. The DU teacher's lawyer Tapas Pal said his client had made the comment when he was talking to wife Monica Bhowmick, after the verdict was handed down. A Dhaka court Tuesday acquitted Nimchandra and 15 students of the same charges. "I won't leave the jail without them (three other teachers)," Nimchandra was quoted by the lawyer as saying. bdnew
